00:43:43.500 --> 00:43:46.530
And I really wanted to.

00:43:46.530 --> 00:43:58.190
So a few words, my book is
about the bill of $1, which

00:43:58.190 --> 00:44:01.160
you may have in your pocket.

00:44:01.160 --> 00:44:06.530
If somebody here has a bill
of $1 in his pocket, $1,

00:44:06.530 --> 00:44:12.470
she or he will find
that on this bill of $1,

00:44:12.470 --> 00:44:13.955
there are three quotes.

00:44:16.620 --> 00:44:23.530
These three quotes, these
three quotes are here.

00:44:23.530 --> 00:44:28.710
The first one is in
Latin, "annuit coeptis."

00:44:28.710 --> 00:44:35.610
The second one is in Latin
also, "novus ordo seclorum."

00:44:35.610 --> 00:44:42.280
And the third one is in Latin
also, "e pluribus, unum"

00:44:42.280 --> 00:44:44.860
on the wings of the eagle.

00:44:44.860 --> 00:44:50.560
So three Latin quotes
in a bill of the most

00:44:50.560 --> 00:44:55.060
materialistic country
in the world--

00:44:55.060 --> 00:45:01.930
these three Latin quotes are
all driven from the same author.

00:45:01.930 --> 00:45:04.870
This author is called Virgil.

00:45:04.870 --> 00:45:10.120
And Virgil is the author of
a book called "Aeneid" that

00:45:10.120 --> 00:45:15.460
tells a story which is,
for me, the founding

00:45:15.460 --> 00:45:21.210
story of the birth,
of the growth,

00:45:21.210 --> 00:45:26.100
of the success of America.

00:45:26.100 --> 00:45:30.180
This is what my book is about,
why there is three Virgil

00:45:30.180 --> 00:45:32.220
quotes of a bill of $1.

00:45:34.740 --> 00:45:36.990
And the book is
also about the fact

00:45:36.990 --> 00:45:42.700
that when you forget the
three Latin quotes on the bill

00:45:42.700 --> 00:45:46.020
of $1, when you forget--

00:45:46.020 --> 00:45:47.820
which is happening today--

00:45:47.820 --> 00:45:52.870
the Virgilian root of the
United States of America,

00:45:52.870 --> 00:45:59.670
in other words, when you forget
that you are a country based

00:45:59.670 --> 00:46:04.890
on the rock of certain
values and principles,

00:46:04.890 --> 00:46:08.700
when you forget that
you, your ancestors,

00:46:08.700 --> 00:46:11.700
your grand grand grand
grand grandfathers

00:46:11.700 --> 00:46:19.585
invented this country in
order to reset Europe,

00:46:19.585 --> 00:46:22.170
because this is
America, those three

00:46:22.170 --> 00:46:26.040
quotes of Virgil on this bill--

00:46:26.040 --> 00:46:31.530
because the idea was to reset
Europe exactly as Aeneas

00:46:31.530 --> 00:46:36.810
did reset Troy, the
city of Troy in flames,

00:46:36.810 --> 00:46:39.510
the city of Amsterdam,
Paris, and London

00:46:39.510 --> 00:46:42.180
in flames in the 16th century.

00:46:42.180 --> 00:46:44.880
And in face of these
flames is the idea

00:46:44.880 --> 00:46:49.620
of reinventing a shining
city on a new land.

00:46:49.620 --> 00:46:52.410
If you'll forget
that, then five kings

00:46:52.410 --> 00:47:02.500
appear, five kings that are
former empires that collapsed

00:47:02.500 --> 00:47:12.730
one after the other, who thought
since decades and centuries

00:47:12.730 --> 00:47:19.780
that they collapse forever,
and who are beginning to think

00:47:19.780 --> 00:47:25.930
that if America withdraws,
if America recedes,

00:47:25.930 --> 00:47:29.560
if America abdicates,
then there might be

00:47:29.560 --> 00:47:35.420
an opportunity for them to
advance, to occupy the field,

00:47:35.420 --> 00:47:38.480
and to fill the vacuum.

00:47:38.480 --> 00:47:41.360
This is what this book is about.

00:47:41.360 --> 00:47:44.850
But it is also about Google.

00:47:44.850 --> 00:47:51.630
It is also about the
fact that the super power

00:47:51.630 --> 00:47:58.530
that a few digital
companies have has something

00:47:58.530 --> 00:48:07.680
to do with this movement
of tide going back

00:48:07.680 --> 00:48:10.200
in terms of geopolitics.

