00:48:19.780 --> 00:48:20.860
AUDIENCE: Thank you.

00:48:20.860 --> 00:48:23.100
Thanks for coming.

00:48:23.100 --> 00:48:27.240
You said something
interesting about "Wikipedia"

00:48:27.240 --> 00:48:32.080
being one of the worst things
we could have as an encyclopedia

00:48:32.080 --> 00:48:34.887
and also that one of the
reasons, If I understand

00:48:34.887 --> 00:48:36.720
correctly, that it's
one of the worst things

00:48:36.720 --> 00:48:39.780
is because "Wikipedia"
is a battlefield

00:48:39.780 --> 00:48:42.480
for vested interests.

00:48:42.480 --> 00:48:46.530
I'm curious how
you think about--

00:48:46.530 --> 00:48:49.590
so the big difference between
"Wikipedia" and Google

00:48:49.590 --> 00:48:53.850
is Google gets most of
its revenue from ads,

00:48:53.850 --> 00:48:57.090
and "Wikipedia" has
pledged over the time

00:48:57.090 --> 00:49:01.050
that it will never
accept ad dollars.

00:49:01.050 --> 00:49:06.210
How do you think about how this
would impact vested interests

00:49:06.210 --> 00:49:12.210
and would impact the truth
that both systems can produce?

00:49:12.210 --> 00:49:14.610
BERNARD-HENRI LEVY: The
worst vested interests

00:49:14.610 --> 00:49:18.310
are those who are
hidden, who are not

00:49:18.310 --> 00:49:21.670
fully and officially expressed.

00:49:21.670 --> 00:49:25.810
An ad, the vested
interest is here.

00:49:25.810 --> 00:49:28.410
It is like a board.

00:49:28.410 --> 00:49:35.050
A vested interest disguised
in self for truth,

00:49:35.050 --> 00:49:36.010
this is the worst.

00:49:38.690 --> 00:49:40.910
This is my reply.

00:49:40.910 --> 00:49:44.500
I have nothing against ads.

00:49:44.500 --> 00:49:48.340
"The New York Times," "Le
Monde," the best newspapers

00:49:48.340 --> 00:49:53.040
on Earth and others have ads.

00:49:53.040 --> 00:49:54.370
It is clear.

00:49:54.370 --> 00:49:56.120
It's open.

00:49:56.120 --> 00:50:02.960
It does not mean that they are
a battlefield for champions

00:50:02.960 --> 00:50:09.550
of so-called pieces of truth.

00:50:09.550 --> 00:50:14.830
Problem of Wikipedia is
that under the appearance

00:50:14.830 --> 00:50:22.210
of neutrality, under the
appearance of everyone,

00:50:22.210 --> 00:50:28.190
of participation,
and under the idea

00:50:28.190 --> 00:50:34.210
that you have an invisible
hand like in the market that

00:50:34.210 --> 00:50:45.440
will be as a referee, correcting
in real time all the excess

00:50:45.440 --> 00:50:48.720
and will reach the
truth under this idea.

00:50:48.720 --> 00:50:52.280
There are some real
intellectual interests--

00:50:52.280 --> 00:50:56.250
I'm not speaking about the
intellectual interests--

00:50:56.250 --> 00:51:02.150
of people who want to
impose or to make advance

00:51:02.150 --> 00:51:05.960
or to give a chance to
something which is a lie.

00:51:05.960 --> 00:51:11.990
I remember Philip Roth,
the great American writer.

00:51:11.990 --> 00:51:16.580
He saw a mistake on
his Wikipedia page.

00:51:16.580 --> 00:51:17.420
He protested.

00:51:17.420 --> 00:51:21.640
He wrote, innocent
way, old world.

00:51:21.640 --> 00:51:26.930
He wrote a letter to Wikipedia
saying, I'm sorry, but see.

00:51:26.930 --> 00:51:31.832
The reply was, you are
not une source fiable.

00:51:31.832 --> 00:51:33.290
BRICE CHALLAMEL:
A reliable source.

00:51:33.290 --> 00:51:37.006
BERNARD-HENRI LEVY: A reliable
source for Philip Roth.

00:51:37.006 --> 00:51:39.890
So this is Wikipedia.

00:51:39.890 --> 00:51:45.440
You cannot make an encyclopedia
if you don't believe that there

00:51:45.440 --> 00:51:47.570
is a ladder, that
there is a scale,

00:51:47.570 --> 00:51:51.090
that there is a hierarchy
in terms of knowledge.

00:51:51.090 --> 00:51:52.820
Nobody has the full knowledge.

00:51:52.820 --> 00:51:54.020
OK.

00:51:54.020 --> 00:51:58.760
Nobody is able to say, I
have the final knowledge.

00:51:58.760 --> 00:51:59.270
OK.

00:51:59.270 --> 00:52:05.320
We all know that the
history of science

00:52:05.320 --> 00:52:08.050
overshadows every
provisional truth.

00:52:08.050 --> 00:52:11.630
At a point, every truth
is a provisional one

00:52:11.630 --> 00:52:14.700
and will be bypassed
by another one.

00:52:14.700 --> 00:52:21.310
But you cannot say that a
provisional truth has the same

00:52:21.310 --> 00:52:30.340
status as a crazy idea just
stemming out of a vested

00:52:30.340 --> 00:52:32.590
interest desire.

00:52:32.590 --> 00:52:34.400
You cannot say that.

00:52:34.400 --> 00:52:40.570
And the problem today of most
of the, especially Wikipedia,

00:52:40.570 --> 00:52:46.960
will have is that it works
under this false idea.

00:52:46.960 --> 00:52:50.800
And we have to restore,
even if it sounds elite.

00:52:50.800 --> 00:52:54.280
I know that you are
a democratic company.

00:52:54.280 --> 00:52:54.822
I know that.

00:52:54.822 --> 00:52:55.530
AUDIENCE: Uh, no.

00:52:55.530 --> 00:52:58.090
We're not.

00:52:58.090 --> 00:53:00.070
BERNARD-HENRI LEVY:
You praise democracy.

00:53:00.070 --> 00:53:01.090
You praise democracy.

00:53:01.090 --> 00:53:01.720
AUDIENCE: Externally, yes.

00:53:01.720 --> 00:53:02.930
But internally, we're
not a democratic company.

00:53:02.930 --> 00:53:05.210
BERNARD-HENRI LEVY: OK, I
don't want to enter in that.

00:53:05.210 --> 00:53:10.810
But to praise the idea
of every point of view

00:53:10.810 --> 00:53:15.830
having to be respected, having
to be praised, and so on, this,

00:53:15.830 --> 00:53:16.330
why not?

00:53:16.330 --> 00:53:19.990
But to be respected does
not mean everyone should

00:53:19.990 --> 00:53:22.720
be respected in expressing--

00:53:22.720 --> 00:53:31.350
his caprice, his belief,
his will to think,

00:53:31.350 --> 00:53:34.970
his hope that the truth
should be this or that,

00:53:34.970 --> 00:53:39.760
but not in the idea that he
has the truth when he did not

00:53:39.760 --> 00:53:45.460
make the process, when
he did not make the path

00:53:45.460 --> 00:53:50.860
and the road that
the scientists know

00:53:50.860 --> 00:53:52.610
and which is the road for truth.

00:53:52.610 --> 00:53:55.030
The two cannot be put
on the same level.

00:53:55.030 --> 00:53:57.880
And there is something
to restore there,

00:53:57.880 --> 00:54:03.130
which is not a reactionary
gesture, but which is, yes,

00:54:03.130 --> 00:54:05.090
a gesture of restoration.

00:54:05.090 --> 00:54:08.590
And it would be great that
the most democratic company--

00:54:08.590 --> 00:54:10.660
one of the most, maybe
another than Google.

00:54:10.660 --> 00:54:14.080
I don't know-- makes
this restoration

00:54:14.080 --> 00:54:18.220
and dares to say
that between Einstein

00:54:18.220 --> 00:54:23.920
and any crazy member
of a conspiracy sect,

00:54:23.920 --> 00:54:27.130
you have enemies.

00:54:27.130 --> 00:54:29.965
This has to be reminded.

00:54:29.965 --> 00:54:31.090
BRICE CHALLAMEL: All right.

00:54:31.090 --> 00:54:32.150
